<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1493,1590]" pageId="2" pageNumber="177">
Two species restricted to the Palaearctic region. The two species have an allopatric distribution with one species occurring in the Maghreb and the other species ranging from southeastern Europe to easternmost 
<collectingCountry box="[1247,1327,1529,1554]" name="Turkey" pageId="2" pageNumber="177">Turkey</collectingCountry>
and from southern 
<collectingCountry box="[254,334,1565,1590]" name="Turkey" pageId="2" pageNumber="177">Turkey</collectingCountry>
to the Levant.
